#   Active ticket board

Index of Beagle's open work: one topic per dir, each holding numbered [Plan]-shaped tickets cleared by the parallel [Issues] fix-and-land loop. Each line below names a topic and its live state; per-topic detail lives in `todo/<TOPIC>/README.mkd`. A fully-landed ticket drops from its topic page; a closed topic drops from here.

##  CRITICAL ‚Äî workflow blockers (2026-06-12 pass: 5 landed, 2 ‚Üí DIS, 1 parked)

These gate the [Issues] loop itself ‚Äî store integrity, clean commits, tip recovery, working clones. A serialized fix-and-land pass on 2026-06-12 landed five in priority order (each fix rebuilt the driver so the binary improved for the next post); two collapsed to spec/design DIS tickets; one is fix-ready but parked on a newly-surfaced weave-merge engine bug.

 -  POST-016 ‚Äî **LANDED `b99e921e`**. `post_classify_step` honored out-of-scope patch/put/mod mtime-stamps, so a selective `be post` swept mtime-drifted-but-unchanged files into the commit (the `?main` contamination). Fix gates the stamp branch on the patch/pd boundary (`SNIFFAtPatchFloorTs`) ‚Äî a commit is now exactly the staged/dirty set. Repro `SNIFFcontam`.
 -  PATCH-002 ‚Äî **LANDED `2583217c`**. `be patch` classified take-theirs/noop from the committed tree-sha triple only, dropping a wt-dirty file the incoming branch also changed. Fix adds a `wt_blob_differs` predicate routing dirty paths into the wt-folding weave (disjoint‚Üímerged, overlap‚Üícontent-conflict). Repro `be-patch-34-dirty-wt-weave`.
 -  PUT-002 ‚Äî **LANDED `1049b261`**. `be put ?#<sha>` ran a vestigial `POST_MIG` ancestry walk and refused unreachable-but-valid shas, ignoring `--force`/`!`. Fix makes it a pure `REFSAppendVerb` (the flat store has no migration to validate). Repro `be-put-05-cross-shard-set`.
 -  PATCH-001 ‚Äî **LANDED `5d5a8d2d`**. `be patch`'s gitlink arm blind-classified every `160000` as noop. Fix stages a forward-moved theirs pin as a take-theirs `put <sub>#<pin>` row (no manual `be put <sub>`). Repro `be-patch-35-sub-gitlink-bump-staged` (ssh).
 -  GET-019 ‚Äî **LANDED `71e49b45`**. `be://` upload-pack summed overlapping pack bookmarks (double-clone-corrupt store) ‚Üí truncated pack. Fix `wire_tile_count`/`wire_bookmark_at` ship the exact closure or refuse `WIRECRPT`; the "stale ?main" facet was the wrecked store, not the wire. Repro `WIREtest_corrupt_overlap`.
 -  SUBS-019 ‚Äî **LANDED `efdd1997`** (hand-picked). `post_classify_step` let a 40-hex gitlink-bump put-row fall through to regular-file handling after a re-mount, recording the empty-blob sha. Fix hoists a gitlink-bump guard. Repro `be-post-39-sub-gitlink-bump-never-empty` (ssh); 360/360 incl POST-016's `SNIFFcontam`. The `be get '?'`/`be patch '?'` FF hit a GET/PATCH base-position fallback (NOT a weave-engine bug ‚Äî see [[DIS-041]]), so the two disjoint POST.c hunks were hand-applied onto trunk and posted.
 -  WEAVE-MERGE ‚Äî **DISPROVEN ‚Üí [[DIS-041]]**. The graf 3-way engine merges the frozen SUBS-019 trio cleanly, byte-identical to `git merge-file`; there is NO weave-engine bug. The real `graf err`/`PATCHFAIL` is a GET/PATCH base+target+cur-position failure (suspected un-indexed-DAG fallback in `build_tip_weave_tunable`, guarded by a `(void)`-ignored `GRAFIndexFromTips`) ‚Äî needs a live repro. Does NOT block landing.
 -  GET-017 ‚Äî **‚Üí [[DIS-039]]**. Premise (switch-shape FF gap) false; the real gap is a spec contradiction (bare `be get` = status per GET.mkd vs Issues.mkd "update first"). No production code; the working form is `be get ?`.
 -  POST-006 ‚Äî **‚Üí [[DIS-040]]**. No byte-level discriminator can exist ‚Äî genuine WEAVE conflicts are emitted inline, byte-identical to quoted markers; needs a provenance-based refusal that couples to POST-016. Forces a verified `--force` when committing files that quote markers (e.g. `sniff/PATCH.c`, hit twice this pass).
 -  KEEP-002 ‚Äî **LANDED `8f7233c3`** (torn-index publish); the original store-integrity blocker, resolved earlier.

